            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Flavoured version: stir in a teaspoon of vanilla, almond, or peppermint extract once the mixture is off the heat."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Dip-coated: once set, dip pieces in melted dark chocolate and let drip on baking paper."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best fresh. Leftovers keep two days in the fridge; reheat covered with a splash of liquid."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Where this dish lives"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Mexican home cooking trusts heat, citrus, and corn. The dish hits those notes — adjust the chilli to taste and finish with a squeeze of lime if it feels heavy."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
